item.title: Help editing!
item.dc:creator: @baseball4355 baseball4355
item.description:
@baseball4355 wrote:

Depends on what source you are using, usually you can change the coords in player.java. So go to the home place where you teleport when you press the home teleport. Dont move from that spot, and get the x coord. Go to player.java, press ctrl and F at the same time and put the coord in there to find it. Then once it finds it there should be a x and y coords. So find the new place you want to teleport to and get the x and y coord and then put them in there. Save and compile and there ya go.
